                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Kitāb-i intiẓām-i ḥayāt by Dodsley, Robert, 1704-1764
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_185-item1">
                     <author key="person_47589" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/47589/">
                        <persName xml:lang="en" type="standard">Dodsley, Robert, 1704-1764</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="trl" key="person_f3318">Translated by <persName type="supplied">Pogson, William, Major Bengal Army</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9664">Kitāb-i intiẓām-i ḥayāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_9664">کتاب انتظام حیات</title>
                     <note>A paraphrastic translation of Robert Dodsley's Economy of human life. Bound in at the front of the manuscript are four folios written by Major Pogson, telling us something of his circumstances and the origin of his translations. When he was Assistant Adjutant General the work was completed with the help of his preceptor, Maulavi Sayyid Karim Husain. It is submitted to the R.A.S. in the hope that it may replace the 'puerile tales and fables' usually provided for students of 'seminaries of Oriental learning.' On European paper watermarked: J. Rump 1825. A paraphrase translation of Robert Dodesley's Oeconomy of Human Life, in Hindustani, Persian and Arabic. Headings and punctuation in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Ay salikan-i khittah-i khak</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>None found.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar hi">Persian (and Hindustani and Arabic. The Persian comes between the others)</textLang>
                  </msItem>
